prompt: Generate Cisco IOS XR 7.0.1 telemetry model-driven configuration for platform inventory + hardware state (FRU inventory entities + operational status). Use gRPC with no TLS. Server 192.0.2.124 port 57500. Use a 2-minute sample interval.
candidate:
telemetry model-driven
 sensor-group PLATFORM-HW-STATE
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven/platform-inventory/fru
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven/platform-inventory/fru/state
 !
 destination-group DG-GRPC
  address-family ipv4
   destination 192.0.2.124
    port 57500
    encoding self-describing-gpb
    protocol grpc no-tls
 !
 subscription SUB-PLATFORM-HW-STATE
  sensor-group-id PLATFORM-HW-STATE sample-interval 120000
  destination-group-id DG-GRPC
 !
rationale: The candidate config correctly uses gRPC no-tls, IP 192.0.2.124, port 57500, and encoding self-describing-gpb, matching the hard requirements. The sample interval is also close (120000 ms = 2 minutes). However, the sensor-paths differ significantly from the expected ones; the candidate uses telemetry-model-driven/platform-inventory/fru and fru/state, while the expectation is for inventory/entities, inventory/summary, and platforms/platform. These sensor-paths are related to platform inventory and hardware state but are not the same and may not fully meet the user's request for FRU inventory entities plus operational status. Therefore, a partial score is given due to correct transport and destination but differing sensor-paths.
